# Shadcn/ui & Tailwind Rules

## ALWAYS use existing shadcn components:

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD
import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button';
import { Card } from '@/components/ui/card';

// ❌ BAD: Don't recreate what exists
<button className="px-4 py-2 border">Click</button>
```

## Use cn() utility for conditional classes:

```typescript
import { cn } from '@/lib/utils';

<div className={cn(
  "base-classes",
  condition && "conditional-classes",
  className // Allow override
)} />
```

## Component Composition:

- Extend shadcn components, don't wrap unnecessarily
- Use variant props
- Follow shadcn patterns for consistency

## Tailwind Rules:

- Mobile-first responsive design
- Use Tailwind's design system (spacing, colors)
- Avoid arbitrary values when possible
- Group related utilities

## File Organization:

```
/components
  /ui          # shadcn components (don't modify)
  /features    # feature-specific components
  /shared      # shared app components
```
